  This README file describes how to use the PhD Thesis LaTex Template
files, along with the Makefile automating the process of compiling
figures, tables and documents.

1. FILES:

  README       This file, of course... ;,D

  Makefile     The file containing the commands to compile all docs
               and which tells "make" what dependencies there are among
               the document files. So if any gets updated, only those
               depending on the file changed will be regenerated.

  thesis.tex   The main LaTeX document, collecting all the customization
               files and the sections documents.

  conf/        The preamble for each draft/final document (PS/PDF/PRESS)
               and customized packages can be found here.

  sections/    Where the LaTeX files for each section can be found.

  papers/      The final PDF version of each publication included in 
               this PhD thesis. 

  figures/     The original LaTeX files to produce the document figures.
               Once compiled, the final PostScript output is saved to "ps"
               directory.

  tables/      In order to get all the tables properly scaled into the current 
               page layout, the best choice is to define them as separate
               LaTeX document and include them as PostScript figures.
               Once compiled, the final PostScript output is saved to "ps"
               directory too.

  ps/          Where all the PostScript final figures/tables can
               be found by "includegraphics".

  docbuilds/   The final documents from each compilation are stored here.


  branches/
  tags/
  trunk/       These three subdirectories are only required if you are
               going to use the "subversion" control version system
               instead of the standard "CVS" (in such case you will have
               a CVS subdirectory).


2. COMPILING:

Type "make pdf" at command-line to produce a new pdf version of the
whole document thesis. The follwoing list shows all the parameters
that can be passed to "make" in order to achieve different results:

   <PARAM>      PROCESS

       all
       pdf
        ps   
     press  
    backup   
     clean
  cleanall
  forceall


